The DA wrote to Parliamentary Speaker Baleka Mbete requesting a motion of no confidence in President Zuma be debated. CAPE TOWN A motion of no confidence in President Jacob Zuma will be debated in the National Assembly this coming Thursday.Democratic Alliance Chief Whip John Steenhuisen wrote to National Assembly Speaker Baleka Mbete to confirm whether the debate will go ahead.He says he received confirmation yesterday afternoon.Steenhuisen has stressed the importance of this move. It comes at a critical juncture in South Africa s political stages because for the first time since 1994 there s widespread dissatisfaction across civil society and business over the president and the state capture revelations that have come up following last year s Nkandla revelation.&quot;(Edited by Shimoney Regter)